		"description": "### Volume API Postman Collection Overview\n\nThis collection provides a comprehensive set of API requests to test volume creation and deletion functionality using the Redfish protocol. It targets a local Redfish service (`localhost:5000`) and demonstrates various volume management scenarios through POST and DELETE requests.\n\n#### üîπ **Collection Features**\n\n- ‚úÖ **Volume Creation** with RAID1 configuration\n    \n- üö´ **Error Handling** for:\n    \n    - Insufficient or invalid number of drives\n        \n    - Duplicate drive usage\n        \n    - Drives from mismatched chassis\n        \n    - Exceeding capacity limits\n        \n- ‚ùå **Volume Deletion** by specific resource path\n    \n\n#### **Authentication**\n\nAll requests use HTTP Basic Authentication with default credentials:\n\n- **Username**: `Administrator`\n    \n- **Password**: `Password`\n    \n\n#### **Intended Use**\n\n- Test storage controller firmware or mock Redfish servers\n    \n- Validate backend logic for volume provisioning\n    \n- Simulate edge cases for RAID configuration",
